ASHBURN, VA- The Washington Redskins made a roster move today. They cut linebacker, Lynden Trail from their practice squad to make room for the signing of cornerback, Deveron Carr. Trail played his college ball at Norfolk State where he started two years for the Spartans. He was an All-MEAC first team selection as a senior where he had 91 tackles to go with 5 sacks. 
Trail signed as an undrafted free agent with the Houston Texans, but was released by the team just before the start of the season. The 6-7, 269 pounder signed with Washington's practice squad on October 5th. Read or Share this story: http://on.wvec.com/1LriUs4 TOP VIDEOS
